Title: Update on Octra HFHE v2 public audit.  Day 6 algebraic track complete: • reduced-param invariant scan (480 samples, 6 keys, 1104 features): 0 survive FDR • ciphertext-algebra toy: 0.000000 TVD between distinct plaintexts • no low-dim simplification lowers the LPN-PRF margin https://t.co/9sJRAuUkIi  URL Source: http://x.com/Kubo100x/status/2077300596064100794  Published Time: 2026-07-15T07:53:51.000Z  Markdown Content: Update on Octra HFHE v2 public audit. Day 6 algebraic track complete: • reduced-param invariant scan (480 samples, 6 keys, 1104 features): 0 survive FDR • ciphertext-algebra toy: 0.000000 TVD between distinct plaintexts • no low-dim simplification lowers the LPN-PRF margin (n=4096, τ=1/8) The wrapper doesn't leak. No equality oracle from algebra. research notes only not a formal audit or security proof. Negative result independently reproduced. No duplicate PRs — smoke-ui already holds INFO-001..005. Contributing the full assessment + reproducible tools to  [@Hikkimori](https://x.com/Hikkimori) open source: [github.com/smoke-ui/octra…](https://github.com/smoke-ui/octra-hfhe-v2-security-assessment) Status: DAY6 PASS. Next = Day 7 freeze. 

